                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/826: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-02T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 2, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. Your 54, September 1. Department has issued denial to the press that a formal
                    ultimatum has been given to the Cuban government. It is hoped that you will be
                    able to avoid statements which can be construed by the opposition as an
                    ultimatum from your Government with regard to a time limit. Department of course
                    thoroughly appreciates the difficulties of the situation, and has entire
                    confidence in you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
